×
DAVID J. COVER, CHAIRMAN AND CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER


David J. Cover is Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Security National Trust Company. Prior to joining Security in 2016,
          he was a Senior Vice President and Market Trust Director for US Trust, Bank of America Private Wealth Management in Providence,
          RI.  He holds a bachelor's degree in Accounting from Penn State University, an MBA from Indiana University of Pennsylvania and a
          certificate in financial planning from The American College.
          
          David is a native of the Johnstown Pennsylvania area.  He has been in the wealth management business since 1986 and has held senior
          leadership positions with various trust organizations since 1999. His background includes significant career stints in a fiduciary
          capacity in Johnstown and York, Pennsylvania, gaining hands-on experience through positions as a trust officer, financial advisor
          with Merrill Lynch (a division of BofA), trust controller, and an early-career position as an accountant. He also led a team of
          portfolio managers for a registered investment advisory firm that served high net worth clients throughout the U.S.
          
          David has been an active volunteer with the Boy Scouts of America, serving on the executive boards of a number of local councils,
          having held the positions of president, council commissioner and council treasurer. In 2011, he was presented with The Silver Beaver
          Award in recognition of his many years of service to Scouting. He has also been a member of the Christian Business Men’s Connection.
        








×
MICHAEL J. COOMBE, PRESIDENT


Michael J. Coombe, CTFA, is President of Security National Trust Company. Mike has over 25 years of wealth management/financial services experience. Prior to joining Security National Trust in 2012, Mike worked for 19 years at Wells Fargo Bank most recently as the Trust Team Manager at the Investment & Fiduciary Services Center in Lancaster, PA. He is a graduate of the Cannon Financial Institute Trust School and is a Certified Trust & Financial Advisor. Mike graduated Summa Cum Laude from Shippensburg University with a Bachelor of Science Degree in Business Administration majoring in finance. Mike is a member of the Lancaster County Estate Planning Council and Lancaster Chamber of Commerce. He is a 20+ year committee chair of the Central Berks American Cancer Society and serves on the grant review committee for the Lancaster Community Foundation.
        








